    summary: 'Medicare charges permanent premium surcharges if you miss your enrollment deadlines without qualifying coverage. Part A penalties last twice the delay period. Part B penalties add 10% per year for life. Part D penalties add approximately 1% of the base premium per uncovered month for life.',
